The paper deals with subspace codes, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on constant dimension codes, which are a subclass of subspace codes and have applications in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the construction of these codes, which involves mathematical structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions optimization of code sizes and minimum distances, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of previously known results, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
